        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 12:43AM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 1243 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aberdeen, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Caledonia, Kolola Springs, and Columbus AFB around 1250 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
northeastern Mississippi.</instruction>
